Mini-API/Frontend: https://github.com/goldenluke/market-qwan

# 🧠 Market-QWAN
### Quantitative Workflow for Adaptive Neural Forecasting

Market-QWAN is an experimental quantitative research platform for:

- 📈 Portfolio-level neural time series forecasting
- 🧠 Regime-aware modeling
- 🌐 Systemic risk monitoring
- 📊 Interactive financial dashboards

The architecture separates **model training**, **visualization**, and **inference**, ensuring stability and modularity.

---

# 🚀 Features

## 🔮 Neural Forecast
- NHITS-based neural time series forecasting (NeuralForecast)
- Configurable:
  - Tickers
  - Input window (context size)
  - Forecast horizon
- Model persistence (`.pkl`)
- Portfolio-level expected return estimation

## 🧠 Systemic Risk Monitor
- Eigenvalue stress (λ_max)
- Correlation heatmap
- Rolling market susceptibility
- Network stress index

## 🌐 External Trainer Interface
- Flask-based training server
- Tailwind-powered UI
- Dynamic model listing
- Asynchronous training execution

## 📊 Streamlit Dashboard
- Clean visual interface
- Forecast visualization
- Model selection dropdown
- Decoupled from training engine

---

# 🏗 Architecture

Streamlit (Visualization Only)
        ↓
Flask Trainer Server
        ↓
train_forecast.py (CLI)
        ↓
models/*.pkl

This prevents:
- Streamlit crashes during heavy training
- Torch subprocess conflicts
- Runtime instability

---

# 📂 Project Structure

market-qwan/
│
├── dashboard.py              # Streamlit dashboard
├── trainer_server.py         # Flask API + Trainer UI
├── train_forecast.py         # CLI training script
├── models/                   # Saved trained models (.pkl)
├── templates/
│   └── trainer.html          # Tailwind trainer interface
├── src/
│   ├── qwan_forecast_model.py
│   ├── qwan_regime_model.py
│   └── ...
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md

---

# ⚙️ Installation

## 1️⃣ Clone Repository

git clone https://github.com/goldenluke/market-qwan.git
cd market-qwan

---

## 2️⃣ Create Virtual Environment (Recommended: Python 3.12)

python -m venv market-qwan-env
source market-qwan-env/bin/activate

---

## 3️⃣ Install Dependencies

pip install --upgrade pip
pip install torch neuralforecast streamlit flask flask-cors numpy pandas plotly scikit-learn networkx hmmlearn statsmodels yfinance

---

# 🚀 Running the System

## 🧠 Start Training Server

python trainer_server.py

Open in browser:

http://127.0.0.1:5050

---

## 📊 Start Streamlit Dashboard

streamlit run dashboard.py

---

# 🔮 Training via CLI (Optional)

python train_forecast.py \
  --tickers AAPL,MSFT \
  --input_size 60 \
  --horizon 10 \
  --model_name model_test

Models are saved in:

models/model_test.pkl

---

